@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Us - CareerTrack Portal";
    Layout = "_Layout";
}

<main class="container">
    <div class="card">
        <h2>About Our Project</h2>
        <p>The CareerTrack Portal is designed to help university students manage their career search process efficiently. Our platform provides comprehensive tools for tracking applications, analyzing progress, and improving job search strategies.</p>

        <div class="data-model">
            <h3>System Data Model</h3>
            <div class="erd">
                <img src="~/images/DataModel.png" alt="ER Diagram Placeholder" class="erd-image">
            </div>
            <p>
                The diagram above shows a one-to-many relationship between students and their applications, and between companies and the applications they receive. It also illustrates how job postings from external sources can be optionally linked to student applications.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="team-section">
        <h2>Our Team</h2>
        <div class="team-grid">
            <!-- Team Member 1 -->
            <div class="team-card">
                <img src="~/images/Arun.jpg" alt="Arun Vijayakumar" class="team-photo">
                <h3>Arun Vijayakumar</h3>
                <p class="email">arunv@usf.edu</p>
                <p class="course">MS in AIBA</p>
                <p>Arun is the backend developer who led the core development of the CareerTrack Portal. He integrated the USAJobs API, implemented the job browsing functionality, and designed the singleton service layer for managing data across sessions. Arun also managed the GitHub repository and oversaw the overall system architecture.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Team Member 2 -->
            <div class="team-card">
                <img src="~/images/Bhavani.jpeg" alt="Bhavani Dande" class="team-photo">
